node.text:
“So many will never understand how much sacrifice has been made to maintain the freedoms so many take for granted. May God Bless America and Bless be the families of our Fallen for they have paved the way. To our Fallen, you will never be forgotten because they are those of us who will refuse to kneel and continue the fight against the evil powers trying to destroy the best country on earth and our people. We will prevail! 

Today let it be a reminder that courage, honor, bravery is the corner stone of our nation best we can offer and our National cemetery’s are this undaunted sacrifice.

Remember them everyday for the day we will forget them, is they day our nation and our people have succumbed to complete tyranny.”

node.text:
Before you say this is not political intimidation, if you’re marching to someone’s office in uniform with a member of the opposing party, that makes it political. If you’re then doing it and there are cameras documenting, you’re being used as a prop. 

This could have been cleared up by calling, emailing, or sending a gift basket. Not this debacle of a PR stunt using the military in order to send a message.

Now, this does not mean you should harass this unit. It pretty clear from my perspective that they were used regardless of their good intentions.

node.text:
Repost @global_surgical_medical_group 
・・・
We are tired of waiting around and we will not stand idly by while others are slaughtered.  This is a time for action. Not thoughts and prayers.  If you know anything about GSMSG, you know we have the teams of US Special Operations veterans and medical professionals who can provide the highest quality medical/surgical care in austere settings and conflict zones.  The clock is ticking in Kabul and because of that we are turning to you the masses to create the change on the ground.  We have created and we’re finally approved for a GoFundMe Page;
 .
.
https://www.gofundme.com/f/afghanistan-rescue-missions-gsmsg
.
.Link is also in our bio.
.
If we can raise the amount needed to charter a large aircraft before time runs out, then we will be wheels up and try to extract as many as your support will allow.  If we don't make the threshold amount to charter a large jet, then 100% of your support will go toward other smaller scale GSMSG operations going forward to extract and recover US and Afghan citizens trapped in the country. At the very least we will try to help cover the $2000 per person “repatriation bill” that is sent by the US state dept to each person flown out.
We have the teams, and we have the track record, now we just need the wings.
Please do what you can, donate, and spread the word.
.
.
.(photo cred to our GSMSG photographer Greg B)
#GSMSG #humanitarian #humanity #Afghanistan
